			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I was just gonna mention the NES' 10NES chip.  That was a very effective method of anti-piracy that was difficult for pirates to circumvent.  To this day, no one has deciphered how the chip actually works, and the CIC chip used in repros is allegedly a clone of Atari's Rabbit chip, itself a clone of the 10NES.  That said, it can be easily bypassed by modifying your console, and some companies used voltage spikes to temporarily knock it out.  It was a very effective form of DRM that was also not very invasive.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
